&lt;section class=&quot;block the-ugly&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;The ugly...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Trump regime accuses Democrats of sedition and calls for their execution...for reiterating the law &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/24/pentagon-says-it-is-investigating-us-senator-over-illegal-orders-video&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Under the Uniform Code of Military Justice, American service members are &lt;i&gt;required&lt;/i&gt; to refuse to obey illegal orders. Since the founding of our nation, our military members have been expected to use their judgment to distinguish between lawful and unlawful orders from their superiors, and can be held accountable for any unlawful actions that they take, even under direct order. This is because we believe our soldiers are capable of understanding which orders are legal and which are not.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;After World War II ended, Hitler&#39;s sycophant&#39;s were hunted down and tried for war crimes. They all tried to excuse their actions by claiming that they were &quot;just following orders.&quot; But that was not recognized on the world stage as a valid excuse for their blatant war crimes. Since that time, our military (like many others) has expended great effort to ensure that our service members know that they have an &lt;i&gt;obligation&lt;/i&gt; to disobey unlawful orders.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Last week, six veterans serving in Congress posted a video in which they each reminded active duty service members that they not only &lt;i&gt;can,&lt;/i&gt; but &lt;i&gt;must&lt;/i&gt; disobey unlawful orders.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The Trump regime&#39;s response was to call these members of Congress seditious and publicly call for their trial and execution. That&#39;s right: Donald Trump&amp;mdash;the same man who pardoned criminals &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2025/jan/24/trump-pardon-proud-boys-enrique-tarrio&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;tried, convicted, and sentenced&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; for seditious conspiracy&amp;mdash;is now accusing sitting members of Congress of the same crime, though they did nothing other than post the following reminder of the &lt;i&gt;standing laws&lt;/i&gt; of our nation.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;div style=&quot;text-align:center&quot;&gt;
