        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Donny 2-Dolls continues to call the Epstein files a Democrat hoax, but has now signed a bill into law requiring the DOJ to release all documents related to Jeffrey Epstein within 30 days.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;For months, the Trump regime has adamantly refused to release these files, fighting tooth and nail to keep the documents classified, drawing ire from Republicans as well as Democrats. They officially lost the fight with the election of Adelita Grijalva to the House of Representatives because she promised she would provide the final signature needed on a petition to force a vote on releasing the files. Mike Johnson delayed her swearing-in for weeks in a desperate attempt to delay the signing of this petition, but eventually had no choice but to swear her in.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Upon realizing that Congress would inevitably vote to release the files, Donny 2-Dolls reversed his position and told his bootlickers that they should vote to release the files. Ever loyal to their Fuehrer, they did not disappoint. The House voted 427-1 to pass the bill, and the Senate passed it unanimously.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;It is expected that the Trump regime will try to exploit a loophole that allows Pam Bondi to withhold or redact documents that jeopardize an active federal investigation or national security. Donny 2-Dolls has already ordered Bondi to open an investigation into Epstein&#39;s associates, and this investigation will probably be used as an excuse to withhold incriminating files. Our prediction: before the year is out&amp;mdash;even while withholding the majority of the documents under this loophole&amp;mdash;Donny 2-Dolls will be taking sole credit for releasing the files and claiming that makes him the most transparent president the world has ever known.&lt;/p&gt;
