        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The Trump regime has repeatedly claimed that their extreme anti-immigrant policies are laser-focused on getting the &quot;worst of the worst&quot; criminals out of our country. But the facts tell a different story.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Of the 600 individuals still being detained after months of brutal raids across Chicago over the past few months, only 16 (2.6%) had any criminal history at all, and none of those criminal charges included offenses that the Trump regime has previously described as the &quot;worst of the worst&quot; (such as rape and murder).&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;U.S. District Judge Jeffrey Cummings has stated that he will order the release of these detainees if the government cannot provide compelling information that they pose a credible threat to public safety.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Chicago residents are infuriated over the violent ICE raids in their communities. They have watched their neighbors, including school teachers, childcare providers, and day laborers, targeted and disappeared in front of their eyes. This includes US citizens, legal residents, and undocumented immigrants who are in the US legally awaiting court cases.&lt;/p&gt;
