    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Mohammaed bin Salman, crown prince of Saudi Arabia, recently visited the White House for the first time since the CIA determined that he ordered the gruesome murder and dismemberment of Washington Post journalist and human rights advocate Jamal Khashoggi in 2018 (and committed other human rights violations). But the Trump regime literally rolled out the red carpet to welcome the prince into the White House.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;When a reporter asked bin Salman about his involvement in the murder of Khashoggi, Donny 2-Dolls interrupted, accusing the reporter of promoting fake news and brushing off Khashoggi&#39;s murder by saying &quot;A lot of people didn&#39;t like that gentlemen that you&#39;re talking about. Whether you like him or didn&#39;t like him, things happen.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Bin Salman handled the question more politely and diplomatically, stating that Khashoggi lost his life for no purpose and that Saudi Arabia has taken steps to prevent such a thing from happening again. He has previously denied involvement in the murder, though he also stated that he takes full responsibility for the act as a leader in the Saudi government.&lt;/p&gt;
