&lt;section class=&quot;block info&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Keeping you informed...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        What happened in Portland? &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.propublica.org/article/portland-protests-national-guard-trump&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Portland, OR&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/6yFIBACOwE-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;112&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:Spicypepper999&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Spicypepper999&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Portland_Oregon_Aerial,_June_2024.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Wikimedia Commons.&lt;/a&gt; Licensed under the &lt;a href=&quot;https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/deed.en&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Creative Commons CCO 1.0 Universal Public Domain Dedication license&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The Trump regime has claimed that deploying National Guard troops to Portland was necessary because  ICE facilities were facing &quot;coordinated assault by violent groups,&quot; leaving the city &quot;war-ravaged&quot; and in desperate need of government assistance.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Evidence shows that in the months leading up to the deployment of the troops to Portland, protesters did clash with counter-protesters, and the police were called in to disperse the crowds. But police were well-equipped to handle the clashes that took place and rarely even made any arrests. No evidence could be found indicating any type of coordinated assault. In fact, after reviewing the case, a federal judge has blocked the deployment of the National Guard to Portland temporarily, until proof can be provided that there is an active rebellion or risk of rebellion against the government or government officials.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Further investigations seem to indicate that most of the violence experienced in Portland came from excessive use of force by police officers. Similarly, masked federal officers have repeatedly been seen using brutality against people who clearly posed no threats to them. In addition, the incidences of violence were notably declining prior to the deployment of the National Guard.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;blockquote&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;The trial testimony produced no credible evidence of any significant damage to the ICE facility in the months before the President’s callout and no credible evidence that ICE was unable to execute immigration laws.&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;figcaption class=&quot;blockquote-footer&quot;&gt;Federal District Judge Karin Immergut&lt;/figcaption&gt;
