&lt;p&gt;Recap of this week in the revolution: Encouraging election results and jury finds &amp;quot;Sandwich Guy&amp;quot; not guilty of assaulting a federal officer. Government shutdowns breaks records for longest in history. Trump flaunts his wealth while SNAP benefits expire for the poorest. What is democratic socialism?&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;section class=&quot;block the-good&quot;&gt;
	&lt;h4&gt;The good...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Encouraging results from key elections nationwide &lt;a href=&quot;https://apps.npr.org/2025-election-results/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;I Voted&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/LaBYB1pCVC-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;133&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://pixabay.com/users/parentrap-2161438/?utm_source=link-attribution&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=image&amp;utm_content=1808671&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Jackie Ramirez&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://pixabay.com//?utm_source=link-attribution&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=image&amp;utm_content=1808671&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Pixabay&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Four of the most significant races in the 2025 elections have been decisively won by Democratic candidates:&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;ol&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;New York City Mayor: &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zohran_Mamdani&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Zohran Mamdani&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;New Jersey Governor: &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mikie_Sherrill&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mikie Sherrill&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Virginia Governor: &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abigail_Spanberger&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Abigail Spanberger&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2025_California_Proposition_50&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;California Prop 50&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;i&gt;Passed&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ol&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;While these elections are encouraging, we do want to point out that this was an off-year election with only a few states or cities that had significant candidates or policies on the ballot at all. Hopefully, these results are a sign that people are fed up with the Trump regime&#39;s assault on American democracy. If this momentum keeps up, it&#39;s entirely possible that the 2026 mid-term elections will significantly change the balance of power in our government.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Related Links:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;ul class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://apps.npr.org/2025-election-results/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(NPR) 2025 Election Results: Live&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
