		&lt;p&gt;The Trump regime is rewriting the rules that govern who is eligible for disability benefits. The argument they are making is that the changes are necessary to reduce the federal deficit and prop up the failing Social Security system, but funds for disability benefits do not come from these sources. In all likelihood, the changes will only push more people into early retirement, causing even more strain on Social Security, while the money saved would sit in the disability benefits trust, unable to be used for other purposes.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The changes are likely to have a disproportionate impact on Trump-supporting states, since many of these states have higher-than-average numbers of workers receiving disability benefits. The proposed changes could cause as many as 1.5 million workers to lose their eligibility for disability benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
