        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;As he promised, Illinois Governor J.B. Pritzker has signed an executive order to create &lt;i&gt;The Illinois Accountability Commission.&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The Commission has three primary missions:&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;ol&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Create a public record of abuses&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Capture the impact of ICE activities on families and communities&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Recommend actions to prevent further harm and to pursue justice&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ol&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Pritzker is known to be a champion of human rights, and this latest executive order is an example of him standing up for those very values as they are being trampled by the Trump regime.&lt;/p&gt;
