		&lt;p&gt;Johnson has made the claim that he will not swear in Representative Grijalva until the shutdown is over, but there is no legal reason or justification for that decision: The US Congress is expected to continue to work even during a shutdown.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The real reason Johnson refuses to swear in Representative Grijalva is because she is expected to vote in favor of releasing the Epstein files, and her vote would push the expected total of representatives in favor of releasing the files to the 218 needed to force a vote on the issue.&lt;/p&gt;
