&lt;h4&gt;The ugly...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Trump&#39;s unfounded Tylenol claims &lt;a href=&quot;https://apnews.com/article/tylenol-cause-autism-trump-kennedy-0847ee76eedecbd5e9baa6888b567d66&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;It can only good happen&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/zUO7jahm8k-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;272&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;&quot;But with Tylenol, don&#39;t take it. Nothing bad can happen, it can only good happen.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Donny 2-Dolls is pushing false claims of a link between Tylenol vaccines and autism, and is urging pregnant women and children to stop taking the drug. He also promoted unsubstantiated claims that childhood immunizations contribute to autism.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The announcement just happens to coincide with the promise by RFK Jr. to &quot;find&quot; the cause of autism &quot;by September.&quot; Kennedy&#39;s efforts to achieve this have mostly revolved around firing the most qualified scientists working for the CDC and NIH. Kennedy has been been saying for years that autism is primarily caused by immunizations, though there is no evidence to support his claims.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The official recommendation made by the FDA is that doctors should &quot;consider minimizing&quot; the use of Tylenol by pregnant women, while acknowledging that &quot;a causal relationship has not been established, and there are contrary studies in the scientific literature.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;As for vaccines, Dr. Susan Kressly, president of the American Academy of Pediatrics said:&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;blockquote&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Studies have repeatedly found no credible link between life-saving childhood vaccines and autism.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Any effort to misrepresent sound, strong science poses a threat to the health of children.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/blockquote&gt;
